President Biden welcomes Prime Minister Ardern to the White House, highlighting New Zealand's leadership in climate change and efforts to curb violence. They discuss the shared history and friendship between their countries, as well as the challenges they face domestically and internationally. Prime Minister Ardern expresses condolences for recent tragedies in the United States and offers support. They also discuss the importance of working together on tech companies, the Indo-Pacific Economic Framework, Ukraine, and climate change. President Biden emphasizes the need for collaboration and expresses a willingness to work with Pacific Islands. The press conference concludes with President Biden stating that he will meet with Congress to discuss gun control.